&quot;Gil Anderson in Stutz Wins At World's Record Speed&quot;
&quot;Indianapolis Product Places First and Second at Gotham Speedway--American Cars Finish in Five Top Positions.&quot;
&quot;Today, Anderson in his Stutz won the opening 350-mile race on the new 2-mile board speedway, averaging 102.6 miles per hour for the distance and beating records made on all other tracks...&quot; 
<i>Motor Age</i>28(16)(14 October 1915): pp. 5-6.
